-- African Sun to Use $10 Million Loan to Refurbish its Hotels
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-02-09T09:14:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/african-sun-to-use-10-million-loan-to-refurbish-its-hotels.html
African Sun Ltd. (ZSI)  will use a $10
million loan from the African Export-Import Bank to refurbish
its hotels, the company said.  The Harare, Zimbabwe-based company will introduce the
 Intercontinental Hotels Group (IHG)  brand in  Zimbabwe  and refurbish
its  Holiday Inn (0080216D)  hotels in the country, it said.  It will also abandon the Holiday Inn brand for two of its
Zimbabwean hotels and will complete work on its hotels in the
first half of this year, the company said.  The company also owns hotels in Nigeria and  Ghana .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Harare at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  